name: PD Salt
commentary: gottim, nicked to the keeper! Pace off does the trick for Ngidi and Royals have the breakthrough. Salt wont' be getting that hundred today, then... big heave across the line but completely mistimed and a thick edge loops through to Buttler

name: BKG Mendis
commentary: sits back on the hack... and holes out to mid-off! Another slower ball, Mendis chooses to go for broke, but he can't wrap his bat round the stroke, as Miller back-pedals to swallow the offering. An outstanding innings comes to an end

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: flying grab in the gully! A short wide ball, an open-faced hack, and old man Eoin sees it straight off the face of the bat, flings himself full-stretch to his right, and plucks a blinder! Well now!

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: bowled him! Tried to get too funky on the ramp, ends up tumbling across his crease to the full length outside off, and deflects the stroke straight into his off stump. Next time maybe...

name: CA Ingram
commentary: yorker, excellently bowled, clipped to deep midwicket, they rush back for the second but no chance. Run out by a distance, but that's a fine final over.

name: JJ Roy
commentary: pinned on the pads, gone! Roy is nailed to the crease by a 152kph rocket, and he's not going to review. Nortje gets this right on the money, completely beats the England opener for pace and he's squared up, rapped in front of middle as the bat scissors down. Trouble for Royals

name: PR Stirling
commentary: picked up leg side, taken at deep square leg! Bosch bangs away on a length and makes the breakthrough for Capitals. Stirling was looking to go across the line and target the short boundary but got it off the bottom of the bat, never enough to clear Muthusamy in the deep

name: JC Buttler
commentary: pulled, top-edged, gone! Is it too little too late, if not for Capitals, then for Durban? Buttler goes for broke as Neesham bangs it in, outside off and fails to get over his stroke as short backward square back-pedals. Still, a magnificent innings in adversity... scratchy at first but authoritative when it needed to be

name: M Van Buuren
commentary: sliced high and out towards deep point - taken! Van Buuren departs after a scratchy knock, went hard at what looked like a slower ball but only succeeded in getting under it. Skied to the boundary rider who takes it safely well in from the rope

name: EJG Morgan
commentary: gets Morgan first up! Tries to launch another attack but holes out to deep midwicket. Legbreak on a length, he was hitting with the spin but nowhere near the pitch and it went high without getting the distance required. Adil Rashid sends his World Cup-winning skipper on his way

name: DA Miller
commentary: scuffs his pull to midwicket! It's a huge wicket in this over after all! Miller swings across the line, but misjudges the pace off what seems to be a more two-paced deck that Mendis allowed it to be in his innings... very high on the bat, and Paarl are on the rocks!

name: AL Phehlukwayo
commentary: a wipe through the line, skied to mid-off! This is a really headless chase from Paarl, Phehlukwayo saw the full length, thought it was in his arc, but the ball was angled across his bows and found a leading edge for Ingram to grab well, scuttling back behind the bowler

name: E Jones
commentary: blinding take from Rashid at fine leg! Short and surprising from Neesham, and Jones was utterly suckered, hurried on the pull, couldn't get his bat through the stroke in time and Rashid hurtles in, tumbles forward and makes it two in the over for Neesham!

name: BC Fortuin
commentary: attempts the reverse sweep with nothing riding on the stroke, and back goes the stumps

name: F du Plessis
commentary: Round the wicket, action straightaway as Linde lands it on a length and gets it to turn viciously outside off, he had to reach for it and spoons it straight to Rashid Khan at short cover, the third umpire is taking a look at it, he dived full-length to take a screamer and the big fish du Plessis goes without scoring! What a start for MICT

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: Another one bites the dust! Dug in short from round the wicket, angled into the body, he flexes his biceps and goes for the pull, Tim David charges in from the rope, tracks the ball from the bat, through the air, towards him and then into his hand.

name: BS Makhanya
commentary: Banged in short, the ball got big on him, he throws his bat at it and miscues a skier, it stays tantalizingly in the air and Rabada gobbles it up gleefully at mid-on region and wickets are tumbling

name: MS Wade
commentary: Dragged on! Archer strikes! Slightly shorter and attacking the stumps, he went for the wild hoick, gets a thick inside edge and chops it back onto the stumps and JSK are four down!

name: D Ferreira
commentary: Nicked behind! Lobbed up, slowed it down and got a hint of turn outside off, lured him into a big shot, he went hard at it to cut that away and got an edge through to the keeper, and Brevis has the last laugh

name: KI Simmonds
commentary: Gottim! Pace off the ball, rolled his fingers on it, tempting him to go for the pull, he is too early into the shot and ends up rearranging his stumps, smarly bowled from the dextrous speedster. Important breakthrough

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: Springs down the track to create his own length, lofts it over mid-on and it looked like he got a good piece of bat on it, couldn't really get to the pitch of the ball and targets the longest part od the ground, finds the fielder in the deep who swallows it up by putting in a slide, Ferreira pouches it well

name: WB Marshall
commentary: Full, nice straight lines, thumping his pads, huge shout for an lbw and the umpire agrees, Marshall takes the review. Pitching in line, impact in line and crashing the stumps so success for Maheesh in his first over, he is keeping it very tight

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: What a ripper! Tossed up, wicket-to-wicket stuff, Roelofsen is pegged back and the deflects off the pads and disturbs the furniture, arms aloft as Simmonds is absolutely ecstatic

name: D Brevis
commentary: Sounds the death rattle! Slower one on a hard length, jags back and pings the leg stump as he plays all over it. Joburg Super Kings register an emphatic win over MI Cape Town, winning by 76 runs!

name: GF Linde
commentary: Knocked him over! On a length, nips back, it kept low and it goes through the gate as Coetzee roars in celebration. He's bowling with steam in his eyes and showing a lot of discipline

name: TH David
commentary: Snaffled by Hendricks! Goes full on off stump and he doesn't need second invitation, goes for the aerial route, gets the height but not the distance on this occasion, brilliant catch as easy you like but this was the last hope for MICT

name: D Potgieter
commentary: Straight down du Plessis throat at long-off as Maheesh continues what he does best, not giving room to free arms, sticking to his tight lines, mixing it up nicely as MICT stare into the abyss and are capitulating under pressure

name: SM Curran
commentary: Another breakthrough! Shorter, quicker on off stump, he rocks back and tries to hoist it over midwicket but it doesn't go over the ropes, another stunning grab from Coetzee as Curran departs for two

name: Rashid Khan
commentary: A low full toss around off, he looks to thrash it over cover, skips down the track but doesn't get the required power and timing behind it, Malan takes a regulation catch at cover, they are checking upstairs if it was a no ball

name: JC Archer
commentary: Edged and taken! Just a fraction short and plugging away outside off, he feet were footed to the crease, slashed hard at it and a thickish edge flew quickly to Wade

name: Q de Kock
commentary: What a brilliant take by Neesham. Full ball on off stump, drives and times it well back to bowler, Neesham took a brilliant one handed catch in his follow through

name: BR McDermott
commentary: Gone! Full and wide outside off, McDermott slices it with an angle bat and it goes straight in the hands of Neesham who took a sharp catch

name: DJ Willey
commentary: That was a fantastic bouncer, short and fast on target, goes for the pull shot, edges it through to keeper, loud shout for caught behind and up goes the finger

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: Take that! Neesham has done it again. Full and wide outside off, Mulder smashes it hard and Neesham at point dives full length and took a one handed blinder!

name: PD Salt
commentary: Gone! Back of length, on middle and leg stump, pulls it away and it goes straight at the throat of deep square leg fielder, Paul took it with ease

name: BKG Mendis
commentary: Gone! Short in length, goes for the pull shot, gets the top edge and bowler calls for it and took it with ease

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: Change of pace does the damage! slower ball, on middle stump, goes for the big shot over mid-on, mistimes it and Willey at mid-on took a simple catch

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: Dala strikes back! Back of length, swings back into the left hander, Rossouw jumps up and cramping for room, thick inside edge onto stumps

name: CA Ingram
commentary: Dala strikes again! back of length, on middle stump, Ingram tries to play a big shot across the line, gets the top edge and Dala calls for it and took it with ease

name: JDS Neesham
commentary: Gone! Neesham tries to play a big shot up and over mid-off fielder, was a back of length ball, wel outside off, mistimes it and de Kock at mid-off took a simple catch

name: S Muthusamy
commentary: Gone! From round the wicket, short in length, on leg stump, Muthusamy flicked it away off his hip straight in the hands of Dala who took it safely. Capitals 8 down.

name: M Pretorius
commentary: short in length, cuts away to deep point and running back for the 2nd run, good pick up and throw by fielder in the deep, keeper flicked the ball onto stumps, shout for run out, tv umpire comes into play and replay shows that Pretorius foot was in the air as the stumps were disturbed. OUT given

name: E Bosch
commentary: Another short ball, he goes for the pull and yet another top edge and this time easy for keeper and Klaasen took it with ease

name: DM Dupavillon
commentary: That is it! Short in length, just outside off, goes for the cut, thick outside edge to third man and fielder makes no mistake

name: F du Plessis
commentary: finds long-off, and falls for 92! The wheels have all but come off for Super Kings in the last few overs. That went flat and fast to the fielder, who took it in front of his head. Fullish and a bit wide of off, as du Plessis went lashing at it with a flat bat. Instead, the ball landed right where the fielder stood

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: swats, but finds deep point! Carse went for a change of pace, and bowled short and wide of off. Hendricks didn't read the cutter, which angled away from him, and ended up giving the fielder a catch, as Hermann got low and took the dying ball

name: MS Wade
commentary: wow, he bowls himself there! A freak wicket, but Markram of course doesn't care. This ball was short around middle and off, as Wade attempted the reverse sweep again. But the length is quite short for that shot, as the ball ends up going on to hit leg stump after hitting his arm and chest

name: D Ferreira
commentary: beaten outside off. Looks to defend this fullish ball angling away, but the ball goes past his outside edge. Appeal for stumping, as they take it to the third umpire. No bat involved - no outside edge for a potential caught behind, that is - and replays show his back leg just rises up and goes in the air when the bails are flicked. Markram strikes twice inside three balls

name: JL du Plooy
commentary: and taken by long-off, just after Markram put himself there! A cutter from Jansen, as he bowls full and a bit wide of off. du Plooy, hanging back deep in the crease, slices that slightly away from his body, with the ball ballooning to the fielder, with the bat face opening. Super Kings losing their way quickly here

name: R Shepherd
shortText: c van der Merwe b Magala
commentary: taken by point! The ball took off from Shepherd's top edge, and the fielder from point just moved a few steps to his right to take it reverse cupped. It was a short ball, which rose well off the pitch, as he pulled, but there looked to be some extra bounce there. Another wicket falls, with more pressure on du Plessis

name: AM Rossington
commentary: Carrom ball knocks over the off stump! Flat on a slight back of length, Rossington took his front leg and looked to push the ball through cover. Played down the wrong line, bamboozled and bowled.

name: T Bavuma
commentary: bowled him, as this keeps low! Bavuma tried to adjust for the lack of bounce, but there was nothing there. It pitched on a fullish length on leg, and turned away to hit the base of middle stump while scooting off the surface. Bavuma was trying to swipe that away seeing the original line and length, but no bounce there - and some turn - got the better of him

name: J Hermann
commentary: Square drive finds point! Full around fifth, there for the slashing stroke. It carved off the outer-half, was going at pace but went around head-height to Ferreira who took the sharp catch. Coetzee and the fielders celebrate.

name: JT Smuts
commentary: Mid-on and mid-off run in, collision. Has the catch been taken? Yes! Bouncer just outside off, Smuts was beaten for pace and bounce. Coetzee and the skipper came in and shaped for the catch in-sync. Coetzee's hair flew as he took the catch. A bit of hip and shoulder but all ends fine, similar to when Shubman Gill and Ravi Jadeja collided while dismissing Wade in the 2020 boxing day Test

name: AK Markram
commentary: slashed to cover-point! Three wickets in three balls. It is falling apart in a hurry. Eastern Cape's last hope departs. The ball was full and wide of off, as he went low to have a flat-batted flash at it. But he only managed an aerial slash to the fielder, who accepted the gift with glee. Super Kings all but confirmed winners from here

name: T Stubbs
commentary: makes room, and is cleaned up! On a short of a length, and going on with the arm to pitch around leg stump. Stubbs was standing outside leg early, and trying to slash that away. But he got a little top edge, with the ball tickling middle stump to leave him frustrated

name: M Jansen
commentary: given leg before as another one stays low! Jansen chats with Markram, and asks for a review. He was hit on his back pad, as he tried to flick that, and replays show there is no inside edge either. The ball was short and pitched just outside off, going on with the arm once again to finish on leg stump while also keeping low. Jansen was deep in the crease as he missed the ball, and ball tracking shows the ball would have pinged leg stump. Two in two for Super Kings

name: JK Fuller
commentary: uproots off stump! They are coming and going here. What looked like a carrom ball was flicked from the front of the hand, and landed on a short of a length. It was angled in, but just hinted to straighten and hit off stump, as Fuller missed his across-the-line clip

name: BA Carse
commentary: popped into Wade's gloves! Good catch, as he moves to his left to calmly take that. This time Shepherd bowled pretty short - following on from a yorker - as the ball angled in and ended outside leg. Carse pulled away from his body, and got a faint glove

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: chopped on! Rassie van der Dussen throws back his head in frustration. Length ball outside off, room to free the arms... but he only managed a thick inside edge into the base of his timbers. Big wicket for Capitals

name: WB Marshall
commentary: gets the first wicket! Bowled according to his field and gets rewarded. Bowls on middle stump giving him no room, tempting Marshall to go over square leg. But there's a fielder in the deep, and when Marshall doesn't get distance on it, Dadswell takes a comfortable catch

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: Little strikes back! Enough of the disrespect, he feels. Bowls it a touch fuller, and a whole lot quicker at 146 kph. Bounces up from quite a full length and hits the top of off. Puts that finger to his lips, and sends Roelofsen on his way.

name: D Brevis
commentary: tried to smash Nortje out of Gauteng, but ends up missing it. Or does he? PC reckon there's a feather on that, and they've sent it upstairs. There is! Brevis falls, and Nortje wins that little battle!

name: GF Linde
commentary: nicked behind! Cramped for room and Linde swipes across the line, gets a thin tickle through to Salt. Neesham gets in on the fun, Capitals well on top now

name: TH David
commentary: full and straight, bowled 'im! David isn't in the same postal district as he backs away outside leg stump. So Nortje fires in a 152kph full toss and smashes the wicket. Neck and crop, David swishes in vain as the ball thunders into middle. Second of the night for Nortje

name: D Jansen
commentary: chaos out there! Curran is dropped at wide long-on... but Jansen has been run out at the non-striker's! Bosch made a mess of a running take going around the rope to his left, but had the presence to field the ball and fire in a flat throw. Muthusamy did the rest with Jansen stuck mid-pitch

name: SM Curran
commentary: straight up the chimney, gone! Short ball angling across and he tries to haul a pull leg side, sends a big top edge into the Centurion sky. Simple take for Salt jogging across towards short fine leg. Sam Curran's poor SA20 continues

name: OF Smith
commentary: clubbed off a length, picks out deep midwicket! Another one goes, severely underclubbed by Smith. Might have been a legcutter from Bosch and he was unable to generate enough power on his hack across the line

name: K Rabada
commentary: slows his pace up, Rabada has a heave and thick-edges through third. Rashid is coming back for three, but KG has been lapped! Both batters at the same end and MI's innings it going to end with a run-out. Very casual from Rabada, who wanders off as his captain crouches over his bat and contemplates a dismal display from his side. In fact, they only got one for that, as Rabada didn't touch his bat in for the second, either!

name: PD Salt
commentary: Miscued by Salt, and his English teammate gets him out. Flew up to KG Rabada at mid-on, who completed a smart catch.

name: BKG Mendis
commentary: brilliant ball. Sigh-inducing, almost. Drifting in, seaming away, squaring him up and taking the top of off. Nigh-on unplayable, and the swagger is back in Curran's face. Puts a finger to his lips to silence the crowd

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: Rashid strikes first ball. Tossed it up, luring him into a drive. Takes the outside edge, and Marshall at first slip holds on after a little juggle

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: miscued and taken! Goes for the big hit again, this time holes out to long-on. Pace on, 142kph and it hurries Rossouw as he aims downtown... gets plenty of height but he's not in control and Rashid Khan settles underneath the catch. A lifeline for MI

name: S Dadswell
commentary: top-edged to square leg, MI have another! Banged in and Dadswell takes on the pull but splices his shot. Rashid is again the man on the spot, scampering across from midwicket to hold it safely sliding on his knees. This chase isn't done yet

name: JDS Neesham
commentary: nicked behind, Smith strikes again! Lovely bowling and Neesham is gone for a two-ball duck. Big roar from the West Indian, he's cracked the game open in this over. Hard length, perfect line and it nibbles just enough, takes the edge and Roelofson does the rest

name: S Muthusamy
commentary: full, sliced to backward point... Curran celebrates, and Capitals are nine down! Unless it was a bump ball? No, it's definitely gone up off the outside edge as Muthusamy chops his bat down into the turf. Snapped up by Brevis, and MI are alive! Sam Curran doing the business with his third of the night

name: E Bosch
commentary: short, wide... and nicked behind! Angling away off the deck, extra bounce from the towering Jansen and Bosch's flat-footed hack culminates in a fat edge through to the keeper. MI still scrapping here

name: A Nortje
commentary: picks out backward point! Makes room and swings hard again, but Brevis intercepts it on the dive! Jansen shushes the crowd, and Capitals still have some work to do. Sliced firmly but well held by the man inside the ring

name: T Bavuma
commentary: That's anticlimactic, strangled by a wide ball down leg. Fullish ball well down leg, Bavuma tried to help it fine but could only tickle it to the keeper.

name: J Hermann
commentary: Soft dismissal, pulled off the bottom of the bat to short midwicket. Was shortish, bounced more than Hermann expected. Was late on it. Got it off the bottom. Spooned to McDermott. Two in two.

name: AK Markram
commentary: Markram finds the middle of the bat and Klaasen at midwicket. Mulder goes ooo, what started to look like a fist pump ended up with palm on the face covering it. Was a full ball on the pads, flicked it off the middle. Went at pace but right to the fielder, knee-height. Simple catch.

name: JJ Roy
commentary: falls finally. Persisted with the wide length as Roy couldn't get much purchase on his shot, getting more height than distance. Ferreira is well positioned to take a smart catch, but let that not detract from a very impressive innings

name: JC Buttler
commentary: that's some comeback! Leg stump knocked back with Coetzee going fullish on off. Buttler cleaned the front leg to go leg side but the bowler cleaned his stumps up instead. But this 21-ball assault has Royals at 53/1 in double quick time.

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: nearly collided but that doesn't prevent a brilliant diving catch around cover by du Plooy. Gripped and turned as he tried to slap it across the line, only to get a leading edge that flew up. There was nearly a mix-up but du Plooy holds on

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: cleans him up with a clever slower ball. Came around the wicket and rolled his fingers over it. Vilas was set up to biff it over midwicket, but misses completely. The top of off line meant the bowler hit

name: D Brevis
commentary: tries to heave it over the covers, but ends up holing out Mulder takes a good catch running backwards, and MICT have now lost both openers

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: Mulder tucked him up and gets the wicket! Roelofsen picked up the length ball with a view to dispatching it over square leg, only to find Keemo Paul positioned well for the catch. It's a bit ungainly but he takes it in the end, and DSG's start gets better

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: ends up skying this to mid-off! Hard, short length, and angling across towards off from Willey, as VDD comes skipping down the pitch. But the bounce was a bit too much for VDD, who was into his pull already. The ball flew off the top edge, with the batter almost cramped there. Easy catch for Harmer, who didn't have to move

name: GF Linde
commentary: comes around the wicket and plays for the spin again. Misreads it again, and Klaasen effects a comfortable stumping. Never really settled, did Linde, and MICT lose another

name: TH David
commentary: a tennis-batted swat to extra cover! Finally Pretorius gets what he was looking for. Good length and a bit wide of off, as David tried to go inside out but ended up with a flat bat, as the ball popped up to the fielder's left

name: Q de Kock
commentary: flashed to point! de Kock falls while playing a reverse sweep. David bowled on a shortish length, while angling it into the left-hander from around the wicket. The ball ended around middle stump, as de Kock switched his bat around only to see the point fielder leap a little to his right to grab that

name: BR McDermott
commentary: takes the pace off and gets McDermott as a result. The Aussie was through his shot too quickly trying to go over mid-off. But Hendricks stretches back, and has the height to pluck a sharp catch out of the air

name: KMA Paul
commentary: Is there life in the game yet? That was actually well timed - he simply used the pace of the bowler to push at that - but still found long-on. Rather, the bat turned in his hands as he went after this fullish ball, which was heading into leg. Yet again, Paul made room to attack but this time found the fielder who took the ball after Smith dropped him last over

name: H Klaasen
commentary: gifted to square leg! Rabada cracks the whip. He banged it in short, and at good pace around middle and off. Klaasen looked to pull, but got that on the higher side of the bat. The ball popped up a little high for a simple catch

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: finds long-on to keep adding to the drama! A low full toss on middle - perhaps a result of an attempted yorker - as Mulder's loft finds the fielder. He was deep in the crease there, and the length was fuller than what he would have liked to go after

name: KR Mayers
commentary: around the wicket, and Mayers meets his end. Tried to lift it over extra cover, but gets an outside edge. Short third takes a smart catch diving forward. Super Kings beginning to apply the brakes ever so slightly

name: Q de Kock
commentary: gets a hold of this, but the deep fielder has been placed very cleverly. It was there to be lofted over backward point, but Quinton needed to clear the ropes to be truly safe, and he can't manage that. Fairly comfortable catch in the deep, and the Super Kings have their first wicket

name: MP Breetzke
commentary: shimmies across his crease, getting outside the line, looking to take the aerial route over the leg side but merely scuffs a simple catch to short backward square. Failed to pick the slower ball and that's an important breakthrough

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: cleans him up with the wrong'un! Mulder was trying to hit him back over his head, but doesn't read the one that spins back in. Sneaks through the gate and clips the top of middle and off.

name: H Klaasen
commentary: fired out wide, Klaasen swings for the hills, but it's straight off the toe! Can't time the cutter, it spirals down to Hendricks at long-on, and the main man falls!

name: KMA Paul
commentary: Maheesh has his man! Paul was all at sea, this time it's the carrom ball, he tries to go big over the covers but miscues into the hands of cover himself, on the edge of the ring. An inelegant slog of an innings comes to an end

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: pounded to cover, to end a baffling innings! A ten-wicket win wouldn't have been a fair representation of this stand, but it's not to be. Still, at least Hendricks found his range in the end. Threw the bat at a wide one, but couldn't pick the gap

name: D Ferreira
commentary: thrashes at the wide one, a thin snick to de Kock! Now then... too little too late? Probably, but a precious dot all the same. Extra bounce on the full length, and Ferreira couldn't control his wild impulses

name: AM Rossington
commentary: caught at mid off! Back of a length delivery angled into the batter. This one hurries onto Rossington too and he does not quite get the elevation he wants. He hits it towards mid off, where Miller times his jump to perfection and snaffles up the chance!

name: J Hermann
commentary: finds the edge this time! No need for DRS! Back of a length delivery just outside off stump. Hermann comes down the track and looks to bash it over the off side. But all he can do is feather it through to Buttler, who makes absolutely no mistake!

name: JT Smuts
commentary: huge appeal, and given! Very full delivery on middle and leg stump. Smuts has a mow across the line but has perhaps picked the wrong ball to do so. The ball, because of the length, sneaks under his bat and smashes into the pads. Shamsi appeals and the umpire has no hesitation in raising his finger. But hang on...Smuts wants to have another look at this! The only thing that can save him is if this pitched outside leg. Nothing on Ultra Edge, and three reds on Ball Tracking! Smuts has to go!

name: AK Markram
commentary: cleans him up! Hard length on off stump that does not bounce as much as Markram expects it to. He has a swipe across the line but is beaten by the lack of bounce, and also by the pace. The ball breezes past the bat and flattens off stump! Markram has a long gaze at the pitch but has to make the long walk back!

name: T Stubbs
commentary: in the air and taken at long on! Full and outside off stump. Stubbs continues to look downtown but toe-ends it very terribly. The ball arrows towards long on, and this time, the fielder makes absolutely no mistake! Massive moment in the game!

name: M Jansen
commentary: taken at long off! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that sticks in the surface. Jansen looks to straight-bat it over long off again but this time, he is hitting against the wind. He gets a decent piece of it but the ball holds up in the air and Bosch does the rest at long off!

name: JK Fuller
commentary: chops it on! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that holds in the surface and just does not arrive. Fuller comes down the track and swings like a rusty gate. He loses his shape completely and ends up chopping it back onto his stumps!

name: JJ Roy
commentary: straight up in the air, and taken! Length delivery outside off stump. Roy comes down the track and looks to go over the bowler's head. The ball, though, holds in the surface and Roy is early into his stroke. The ball lobs up off the toe-end and Erwee makes no mistake at mid off!

name: JC Buttler
commentary: knocks him over! Oh my, what a moment in the game! Slowed up on a length on middle and leg stump. Buttler hangs back in his crease and tries to manoeuvre it into the off side. He is just too early on the stroke, though, and misses a straight ball. It then crashes into middle and leg stump, and van der Merwe is absolutely pumped!

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: huge appeal, and given! Very full delivery on middle and off stump. Lubbe tries the cheeky reverse sweep but makes a hash of it. He picks the wrong length too, before missing the ball and getting rapped on the pads. The umpire has no hesitation in raising his finger but Lubbe wants to go upstairs! Nothing on Ultra Edge, and the impact returns as Umpire's Call. The ball, according to Ball Tracking, would have hit the stumps too and Lubbe has to walk back!

name: M Van Buuren
shortText: c van der Merwe b Magala
commentary: in the air, and taken comfortably! Length delivery on middle and leg stump that sticks in the surface. van Buuren, like many before him, closes the bat face too early and spoons it off the leading edge towards extra cover, where van der Merwe does the rest!

name: AL Phehlukwayo
commentary: holes out to deep backward square leg! Length delivery on leg stump. Phehlukwayo has a swing at it and gets decent enough contact. The only problem, though, is that he hits it straight down Fuller's throat at deep backward square leg!

name: BKG Mendis
commentary: superb work on the fence, finally! Back of a length delivery on off stump that seems to hurry onto the batter. Mendis has a swipe at it but clogs it a touch. Rickelton judges the catch to perfection at deep mid wicket, takes it at the first go and then flicks it back to Linde as soon as he realises that he will step onto the boundary cushion! But has he managed to do so? The third umpire is having multiple looks at it before agreeing that the fielder has pulled it off successfully!

name: WG Jacks
commentary: edged and taken! Back of a length delivery in the channel that might have nipped away ever so slightly. Jacks has a nibble at it without much foot movement and gets a feather through to the keeper. Smith is over the moon; Jacks is not very pleased with his stroke. Massive moment in the game!

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: Rashid gets Rossouw! Length delivery on middle and off stump that skids through. It looks like Rossouw has not picked it again and goes back to a ball he should have been forward to. He is nowhere close to the ball in the end as the ball smashes into the pads in front of middle and off stump. The umpire raises his finger, and Rossouw does not even bother with the review! That looked plumb!

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: picks out short fine leg to perfection! Another very full delivery outside off stump, and de Bruyn looks to repeat the stroke. This time, though, he cramps himself for room a touch and the fullness means he can't quite get under it. He arrows it straight to short fine leg, who makes no mistake!

name: S Muthusamy
commentary: what a ripper! And Archer brings out the Marcus Rashford (and Bukayo Saka from yesterday) celebration too! Length delivery angled into the batter on off stump. On pitching, though, this one snakes away and squares up the batter completely. Muthusamy dangles his bat out, more in hope than anything, and ends up feathering it through to the keeper!

name: C Fortuin
commentary: 500 T20 wickets for Rashid! Full and outside off stump. Fortuin, who has been feeling the pinch in the last few overs, has another wild hack at it. But he swings too hard and is nowhere close to the pitch of the ball either. He ends up dragging it onto his stumps. Take a bow, Rashid Khan!

name: WD Parnell
commentary: Archer gets another! Slower delivery dug into the track on leg stump. Parnell looks to get inside the line and help it past short fine leg but ends up hitting it straight down the fielder's throat! MI Cape Town continue to chip away at the wickets!

name: E Bosch
commentary: Bosch bites the dust! Slower delivery on a back of a length outside off stump. Bosch continues swinging but he is again too early into the stroke. The ball skews up off the outside edge and swirls towards backward point. Rickelton calls early and completes the catch!

name: D Brevis
commentary: Nortje breaks the game open, what a bowler! Nortje has been bowling thunderbolts all tournament but on this occasion, he brings out this canny leg-cutter that Brevis has no clue about. In fact, it is the last thing he is expecting and he is a week early into the stroke, eventually spooning it straight to extra cover. What a huge moment in this game!

name: RD Rickelton
commentary: soft dismissal! Back of a length delivery angled across outside off stump. Rickelton looks to work to leg but because the ball sticks in the surface, he ends up getting a tame leading edge that nestles into mid off's palms! Just the wicket the Capitals needed inside the powerplay!

name: SM Curran
commentary: knocks him over with an absolute peach! Given a bit of air on a length just outside off stump. Curran thinks he has enough width to work with and is shaping for the cut. The ball, though, pitches and spins back a mile, going past Curran's flailing bat and crashing into the stumps! Curran can't quite believe what has happened but he has to walk back!

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: huge appeal, and that looks very adjacent! Full delivery on middle and leg stump. van der Dussen walks across his stumps and then misses the ball altogether. The ball smashes into the pads and to the naked eye, it looks very out. van der Dussen, though, wants to have another look! . Nothing on Ultra Edge, and three reds on Ball Tracking! van der Dussen has to go! That pitched just in line but the Capitals will not care one bit!

name: GF Linde
commentary: skies it, and taken at long off! The Jacks gamble has worked! Given plenty of air on a length. Linde's eyes light up and he looks to go downtown. He is not to the pitch of the ball, though, and has to reach out for it, meaning that he slices it miles up into the air. Long off settles under it, and completes the catch!

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: taken at deep mid wicket! Flighted beautifully on middle and leg stump, and that length entices Roelofsen to have a go at it. Much like Linde, though, he is not close enough to the ball to generate the requisite power. In the end, he skies it towards deep mid wicket, where the fielder does the rest!

name: OF Smith
commentary: flattens off stump! Low full toss that hones in on off stump. Smith continues swinging like a rusty gate and much like the rest of his innings, he does not make any contact. The ball breezes past the bat and thunders into off stump!

name: Rashid Khan
commentary: Rashid bites the dust! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that hurries onto the batter. Rashid has an agricultural hack at it and is awfully late on the stroke. The ball spoons up off the leading edge and Bosch completes an easy catch at extra cover!

name: JC Archer
commentary: straight to mid off! Three for Nortje! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that rushes onto Archer. He tries to muscle it over mid off but because he can't complete his swing, he ends up hitting it straight down Parnell's throat!

name: K Rabada
commentary: that will be that! The Capitals win, and they pick up a bonus point! Full toss slanted into middle and off stump. It seems that Rabada is not expecting that length and is late on the stroke. The ball whistles past the bat and then leaves the stumps in an almighty mess!

name: AM Rossington
commentary: Free hit is full and wide, slashed again. Rossington runs for the second, Hermann is still at the other end. Keeper gets the throw, sends it to the bowler who dislodges the bails as Rossington runs back. Rossington is walking, he's out on a free hit! Replays show he's well short. Good take from Mulder, who went low to the left, swung his hand to the other side. It was a low, wide full toss that was outside the tramline. Rossington reached out and laid the horizontal bat on it. Hermann called out 'no', but Rossington turned and ran quickly.

name: J Hermann
commentary: Two-in-two! Excellently-judged by Holder at long-on and that's the end of Hermann! Pretorius bowls it full and outside leg, Hermann once again backs away to hit it straight over. But ends up getting more height than distance. Holder has his eyes on it and takes it, but seems to be losing his balance and throws it back to Klaasen at long-off . The TV ump has a couple of looks and is convinced.

name: KR Mayers
shortText: c Stubbs b van der Merwe
commentary: Stubbs, you beauty! Runs in, dives forward and hangs on to a terrific catch to give van der Merwe his fourth. He darts it short on off and middle, Mayers goes back to pull it over deep midwicket, which is the longest part of the field. Finds the lone man there and that sets van der Merwe running.

name: MP Breetzke
commentary: Bowled! Goes across too far and misses the sweep! Markram is pumped. Saw the batter go across early, got it wide on a length and ragged it in. May have got a bit of glove on the way. Disturbed the woodwork.

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: Mulder finds short third! Magala's sharp, leaps to the left and plucks it. Athletic catch brings out celebrations and cheers from the crowd. Was on a length, wide. Mulder slashed hard. The edge off the cut was in Magala's reach and he took it low.

name: H Klaasen
commentary: Off pole knocked, van der Merwe is ecstatic! Given air, landed on a length around middle. Turned away, Klaasen cleared his front leg and tried to pull it. Went a bit lower than he expected and sent the bails on a flight.

name: Q de Kock
commentary: Big LBW appeal, given! QDK reviews. Very full ball, beat de Kock on the sweep. This one looked to have pitched in line. Looked to have gone on with the arm. Pitched on middle and leg, impact in line (hit the pad low, under the knee roll), hitting the inner-half of off stump. Finger goes up. Sunrisers have had the perfect game thus far.

name: JO Holder
commentary: Skied, van der Merwe goes to midwicket. Gets under it and takes it! Length from around the wicket, spun away a bit to around off. Holder went for the slog sweep, top edged it. Van der Merwe got there, was limboing as the ball was coming down. Took it fingers pointing up and roared in celebration.

name: D Pretorius
commentary: Five-wicket haul for van der Merwe and he will be unstoppable tonight. Lands it on a fullish length around middle and leg and gets it to turn away. Pretorius goes back to punch it but is beaten on the outside and is bowled. Van der Merwe likes it and it is the first five-for in the SA20.

name: KMA Paul
commentary: More catching practice for Sunrisers' fielders. Lands this on a length around middle and leg, Paul gets down to play the sweep. Makes good contact but hits it straight down deep backward square leg's throat.

name: P Subrayen
commentary: Wicket No. 6 for van der Merwe! Fires it full on off, Subrayen charges down for a heave but misses it completely. Sees his off stump pegged back and boy, does van der Merwe like it!

name: A Dananjaya
commentary: All over! Huge 124-run win for Sunrisers. Floated full around middle and leg, Dananjaya slinks down and flicks it straight to midwicket.

name: BKG Mendis
commentary: Oh, David Miller, that is a stunning catch! And, it is the all-important wicket of Mendis. Leg-spinner that turns into him sharply. Mendis looks to work it away, gets a bit of a leading-edge. The ball seems to be falling in no-man's land, but Miller runs back from square leg, dives full-length and snaps it up one-handed, inches from the turf.

name: WG Jacks
commentary: Oh, loud, loud appeal as Jacks is hit right in front of the stumps! And, the umpire agrees. Jacks has reviewed, but I think more in hope. Yes, DRS confirms the ball would have smashed into leg stump. Angles this into the batter, who gets across looking to push it to the on-side. Misses, and once that happened, it was always going to be trouble for Jacks. So, Fortuin, the highest wicket-taker of the competition, nabs the highest run-scorer.

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: slower ball that appeared to be in the hitting arc, but he's somehow holed out to deep midwicket, where a terrific catch is taken. It almost seemed to hold up in the wind, which allowed Lubbe to scamper to his right and then leap forward to get rid of the dangerous du Bruyn

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: too clever by half! Did a cocky little jig before Adams entered his delivery stride, but Adams holds his nerve, takes the pace off, and sneaks through the gate and removes his off stump

name: S Dadswell
commentary: pace off wide of off does for Dadswell completely. Goes through his swing much too early and skies it towards mid-on, where Miller takes the simplest catch

name: E Bosch
commentary: Ngidi puts Bosch out of his wretched misery. Another wild onside swing, another wider ball from Ngidi. This time he gets a faint tickle on it, and walks off before even the umpire has time to raise the finger

name: JJ Roy
commentary: Chops it back onto his stumps, and Roy departs! Rolls his fingers over back of a length ball outside off. Roy has not picked it as he backs away looking to thrash it away. Is through the shot early and can only inside-edge back onto his stumps. He was looking good, but has to go back now.

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: A super take from Mendis, as they collectively go up for a caught behind! Not given on the ground, but Parnell reviews. Has that taken the glove through to Mendis? Looks like it has. Rashid floats it a touch slower outside off. Lubbe gets across and sets up for a reverse sweep. The ball hits his pad first and then rolls on the glove through to the keeper. Excellent review and Rashid has struck in his first over.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: cleans him up, what a spectacular over this has turned out to be. Flighted the ball, which grips and squeezes through the gate between his bat and pad

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: Will Jacks strikes first-ball. It was slow and short, with Vilas looking to clobber it over deep point for six. Never really gets enough distance on it, though, and that's a vital wicket for the Capitals as a strategy break is called

name: AM Rossington
commentary: tried to pull it away but it kept low, and it tickles the under-edge in the process! Didn't look like the umpire was going to give it, but he's walking! Brings a good-looking innings to an end and it's a huge wicket for the Super Kings

name: J Hermann
commentary: and gets a wicket first ball! Tried to lift it over mid-off, but it got up high on the bat and popped up straight to Joseph stationed there

name: SJ Erwee
commentary: it's a mix-up, and Erwee is run-out after utter confusion. He called for one but couldn't quite commit, and the stop-start nature of his stride meant he was never ever going to make it. du Plessis put in a great dive to stop at mid-on, and it was curtains for the batter

name: AK Markram
commentary: skies this one. It dug in short and his head was badly out of position. Manages to get only elevation, no distance, and the Sunrisers lose another after the keeper makes no mistake

name: T Stubbs
commentary: Jaffa, and he is gone! Tossed up on a length on off, Stubbs came down the wicket but the ball spins sharply away from him. Keeper whips the bails off quickly, and Phangiso is on a hat-trick!

name: JT Smuts
commentary: That's another for Phangiso! Smuts looks to reverse-sweep but gloves it up and Ferreira gobbles it up. Four for the spinner and Sunrisers lose their seventh

name: M Jansen
commentary: Skied, and taken! Flighted on a length outside off, Jansen looks to slog-sweep that but top-edges it high in the air. Ferreira settles under it and that's an easy catch. Phangiso has his third!

name: JK Fuller
commentary: Hit straight to long-off! And that will be that for Sunrisers East Cape. That was a slower ball, full and wide, Fuller gets low and looks to hoick it down the ground, but it's not straight enough and goes straight to that man Faf du Plessis. He takes it reverse-cupped while crouching down. This was relatively straightforward for him!

name: BA Carse
commentary: Bowled 'im! On a length outside off, jags in sharply and takes the top of middle! Carse was thinking it would be shorter and he had to bring his bat down quickly, but can't get it down quick enough

name: RE van der Merwe
commentary: No mistake this time! It's a blinder from Faf du Plessis! Full outside off, he swings through the line but doesn't time it. Faf runs back from mid-off, and dives to get under that and hold on. He has been just so good in the field today

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: In the air, and taken! Magala with the breakthrough. Goes full outside off, Hendricks looks to drive it square, but gets an edge that loops up and Stubbs takes a nice catch diving forward at deep backward point

name: F du Plessis
commentary: holes to long-on, and that feels like an important wicket. Perhaps the ball was a touch too short to drive through the line like that, but du Plessis is good enough to have pulled it off. The ball hits the toe of the bat and the giant figure of Marco Jansen catches comfortably

name: N Brand
commentary: He's hit that onto the stumps! Length ball on leg, he gave himself a lot of room and looks to carve it away on the off side, but ends up crashing it onto the stumps!

name: BS Makhanya
commentary: outstanding work in the field leads to a run-out! Makhanya's left stranded in the middle of the pitch!. The ball bounced kindly for him, and he picks up and throws with such speed it makes the running look a bit daft. SEC are well in this now

name: D Ferreira
commentary: comes down the wicket and he has a swing and complete miss! He's so far down the wicket there's no way he's getting back in time, and Rossington effects the stumping. There's another twist here

name: RD Rickelton
commentary: he's scooped it straight back to Fortuin. Went through the shot a bit early, and it pops up straight back to Fortuin. An over that began with a boundary ends with a wicket

name: D Brevis
commentary: drifts in, holds its line, and traps him plumb in front. There's no doubting that, but Brevis still goes for a ridiculous review, to be honest. A review isn't a Magically-turn-out-into-not-out card, even if some players treat it like that. Yep, it's not saved him, and MICT's horror start gets worse

name: SM Curran
commentary: drags this one down, but what on earth is that running? Sam Curran heads of for a run that Brevis sends him back for. Curran went so far down the pitch without Brevis moving it was a bit ridiculous. Curran nowhere near as Fortuin whips the bails off at the non-striker's end

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: almost an action replay of the last ball. Even poorer connection this time and it's a straightforward for Miller. In fact, he had to take half a step forward as it was dying on him. Goes on his knees and gobbles it up

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: falls for 49. Backs away this time and throws his bat at it. Gets more of an outside edge and Roy makes no mistake at backward point

name: GF Linde
commentary: Shamsi bounces back in style. Bowls a wrong'un. Linde tries to repeat the shot, looking to slog sweep it over midwicket once again but misses and the off stump had been knocked back

name: D Potgieter
commentary: Shamsi conjures up his magic again. This time doing the batter in the flight and beating the outside edge with the turn. Potgieter was drawn out of his crease and failed to get back in time

name: OF Smith
commentary: impressive catch by Adams at backward point. Was slow, full and wide. Smith went after it but couldn't keep it down. Adams went low to his right and grabbed it with both hands

name: Rashid Khan
commentary: a slower one outside off and Rashid goes aerial. Fails to middle it though and Miller who is halfway to the boundary at long-off pedals back, pouches it and falls on his back

name: JJ Roy
commentary: holes out to long-off. It's the sort of ball Roy would have comfortably deposited over the ropes in his heyday, but finds the fielder at the boundary this time. Was there to be hit, but as he stepped away to loft it over the fielder, just found a touch more height than distance

name: JC Buttler
commentary: that should be the game. Full outside off, Buttler tries to give himself some room to go inside out. All he manages is an outside edge to the keeper

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: has he bowled him? It's supposed to be the most obvious dismissal, yet no one seems to have realised it's taken the leg bail. Lubbe looked to pick it up over short fine leg, but played all around the ball, which kisses the bail. The keeper is the first one to spot it, and just like that, Linde's on a hat-trick

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: cleans him up! It had been a struggle for Vilas all innings, Rabada puts him out of his misery. Tried to run it down to third man, but gets an inside edge and chops it on

name: M Van Buuren
commentary: absolutely unplayable. Lovely flight, in that perfect zone where the batter's feet get frozen, and to top it off, it's a googly that tucks him up and whooshes through the gate and clips the top of the stumps

name: DA Miller
commentary: a huge wicket. Full around off and Miller goes for the big hit. Ends up miscuing it and Archer takes a couple of steps back at long-on and catches it with fingers pointing upwards

name: KR Mayers
commentary: first ball wicket! What a decision to bowl Parnell with the new ball! Surprises Mayers with the short ball, aimed at Mayers' shoulder. He tries to nudge it leg side, but it takes a top edge and flies to Rashid at third man!

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: full ball on middle and leg. Misses the flick, hits the front leg, and LBW appeal is turned down. Are they reviewing? Oh yes! And the review is worth it: landing on leg, hitting on leg, and going onto hit leg stump. Umpire has to change his decision.

name: Q de Kock
commentary: that's three down - and de Kock's stumps are rattled! This was full and fast. In the slot for de Kock to slog across midwicket. But the ball moves just a tad into de Kock, and he has been #castled

name: H Klaasen
commentary: tries to smear it back down the ground, but gets nowhere near a Rashid ball that keeps low and skids along. Makes the shot look particularly agricultural as the ball clatters into the base of off stump. Was that the Super Giants last hope of a competitive total?

name: JO Holder
commentary: smart bowling! Pushing it wider outside off, forcing Holder to reach at it. Holder comes down the track and with the ball turning away, he has to really stretch out. He's committed to the loft, and therefore can't pull out of the shot. High in the air, and deep extra cover runs in to take a catch at knee height. Holder is gone and that's time for the strategy break

name: C Jonker
commentary: . That was a soft dismissal. Looked to drive through the line of the ball but neither manages to keep it down nor get any elevation on it. As a result it's straight back for the simplest caught and bowled you could ever see

name: D Pretorius
commentary: oh dear. Everything they touch is turning to dust. This ball looked like it was there to be hit. Full, in the slot. But Pretorius only slices it to short third as the last recognised batter trudges back

name: KA Maharaj
commentary: short of a length, sliced to deep point - has Dadswell caught it? What a catch that is. Looked for all the world like it was dropping short, but he gets his fingers underneath it and actually ends up doing it quite comfortably. Sensational display from the Capitals, restricting the Super Giants to the lowest score of the tournament

name: GC Viljoen
commentary: tucks him up, forcing Viljoen into scooping one high to midwicket. That got much more elevation than it did distance, and the catch is completed comfortably by Dadswell in the deep

name: P Subrayen
commentary: it's two in two! That was a slower delivery that Subrayen played down the wrong line to. It struck him on the pad and the umpire gave it straightaway. Might be sliding down leg, though. Hawkeye tells us that it is just clipping, so the out decision stands!

name: PD Salt
commentary: long on and deep square leg the two outfielders. Mayers goes full just outside off and Salt looks to hit it over mid off. Uh oh, toe-ended to mid off! That's a first baller

name: WG Jacks
commentary: it was there for the finishing, but Jacks holes out this time to cow corner. Another one short of a length, but Jacks didn't middle one for once. Departs, but not before he's single-handedly made a mockery of this chase

name: JJ Roy
commentary: Cleans him up and Roy's misery continues! Slow, straight ball, Roy lines up for a massive slog sweep. Is beaten altogether and sees his stumps in a mess. That was not the best of shots to put it mildly and Royals have lost both their openers.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Has Carse pulled off a stunner? Oh, he has. Buttler is walking back! Length ball on middle and leg. Buttler gets across and mistimes his clip again. Once again, it seems the ball will fall in no man's land but Carse springs across, dives to his right and completes a one-handed stunner low to his right.

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: Drags it on and Carse celebrates! Another skiddy back of a length ball outside off. That kept a bit low as well as Lubbe looking for a big pull shot, can only chop it back onto his stumps. Just as Royals were crawling back into the game, Sunrisers strike again.

name: C Bosch
shortText: c Jansen b van der Merwe
commentary: Goes high, very high in the air and Jansen gobbles it up! Tossed up just a touch outside off. Bosch goes for a wild slog, but does not get under it. Gets a big top-edge and Jansen at deep midwicket catches it comfortably, reverse-cupped.

name: EJG Morgan
commentary: Falls to the pull, and Royals slip further! Banged in short, Morgan looks for a hook, but has no timing on it. Probably got it off the high part of his bat and Jansen, at deep midwicket, takes a comfortable catch. The sun was right in his eye, but he did not care.

name: DA Miller
shortText: c Cox b van der Merwe
commentary: Oh, dear! Miller couldn't have picked out long off any better! And, Van der Merwe strikes again. Tossed up on off, he was looking to loft it inside out. But gets beaten in the flight and by the slowness of the Paarl surface. He mistimes it straight down the throat of Cox. Miller departs and Royals are firmly behind the eight-ball.

name: E Jones
commentary: Two for Markram. He can't put a foot wrong today! Fired in on leg stump. Jones comes down the track, gives himself room and swings it away. But he is nowhere near it and ends up mistiming it. The ball goes very high into the sky and deep midwicket fielder catches it easily.

name: AM Rossington
commentary: dragged on, Ngidi gets one! Slower ball, Rossington hauls across the line and thick-edges into his off pole. Beautifully bowled, the batter throws back his head to signal that he's been done. Rossington trudges off, Sunrisers lose their first

name: J Hermann
commentary: sliced to backward point, Fortuin has another! Pushed full and wide of the left-hander and he throws the hands, but can only skew his connection towards the man on the edge of the ring for a low catch. Sunrisers have lost both set batters in the space of four balls!

name: SJ Erwee
commentary: castled! Two in two for Ngidi! Things are going Royals' way now... Perfectly bowled cutter from round the wicket and Erwee is left groping at thin air. Fired in with a flick of the fingers and it just holds its line enough to beat his forward prod and topple off stump. Pearler

name: AK Markram
commentary: done in by a shooter! Speared into the pitch and Markram was back, and comprehensively beaten as the ball skidded on low into middle stump. Have Royals given themselves a glimmer of hope?

name: JM Cox
commentary: dragged on first ball! Cox is back in his box and Royals are still scrapping in this contest. Length ball outside off and he's slightly cramped as he attempts to cut, a fat bottom edge cannoning into the base of off stump. And now Fortuin is on a hat-trick!

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: gone first ball, oh my word! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that leaves the batter very late. Hendricks has a nibble at it without any foot movement and feathers it through to the keeper. What a start this is for the Capitals!

name: F du Plessis
commentary: and Neesham answers the Capitals' clarion call! Length delivery outside off stump that might have just moved away a shade. du Plessis has a waft at it without much foot movement and gets a thick outside edge that is snaffled up by Salt!

name: JL du Plooy
commentary: du Plooy bites the dust! Back of a length delivery on middle and off stump that gets onto du Plooy a lot quicker than he expects. He advances and has a hack across the line, only managing a tame splice to mid on in the process!

name: K Verreynne
commentary: chops it on! Back of a length delivery outside off stump. Verreynne looks to force it through the off side but his cut stroke lacks conviction, and footwork. In the end, he drags it onto off stump, and the Capitals are now firmly in the ascendancy!

name: L Gregory
commentary: two in the over! Neesham is on fire! Not quite a picture-book dismissal but Neesham will not mind. Angled down the leg side and all Gregory has to do is tickle it past the keeper. Instead, he helps it off the face of the bat towards Salt, who flies to his left and completes a smart catch!

name: D Ferreira
commentary: cleans up Ferreira with a beauty! Flighted beautifully on a length on middle and off stump. Ferreira's eyes light up and he looks to tonk that into next week. However, he does not quite gauge the flight properly and is nowhere near the pitch of the ball. It spins past the bat and then pegs back off stump! The Super Kings are EIGHT DOWN now!

name: R Shepherd
commentary: miscued and Nortje pouches it at third man! Full and angled into the batter on middle and off stump. Shepherd has an ugly swipe across the line and gets a massive leading edge that arrows towards third man. Nortje races in off the fence, slides forward and completes the catch!

name: G Coetzee
commentary: soft dismissal, oh dear! Slower delivery on a length on middle and leg stump. Coetzee has no clue about this one and it also seems to stop in the surface considerably. Coetzee dangles his bat and pops it straight back to the bowler!

name: AS Joseph
commentary: oh, what a catch! Stop the press, I simply cannot believe that! Slower delivery on a full length outside off stump. Joseph throws his hands at it and slices it towards backward point. For the longest time, it seems as if the ball is going to evade Neesham at backward point. Well, until he decides to channel his inner superhero, soar to his left and pluck it out of thin air, one-handed! No adjective can ever do justice to that catch!

name: N Burger
commentary: that will be that for the innings! Googly flighted on a full length on middle and off stump. Burger looks to go inside out but is not to the pitch of the ball. In the end, he chips it straight to short extra cover

name: WG Jacks
commentary: straight to deep point! Full delivery on middle and off stump. Jacks backs away and looks to carve it over deep point. He gets decent contact but can't elevate it enough to beat the sweeper at deep point. Fairly regulation catch for du Plooy and the Super Kings have the wicket they were after!

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: oh dear, what has happened here?! Full delivery just outside off stump. Salt smacks it straight back to the bowler, who gets his boot in the way and somehow manages to deflect it onto the stumps at the bowler's end, with de Bruyn well out of his crease! What a strange dismissal, and the Super Kings suddenly have two in quick succession!

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: knocks him over! Full delivery on middle stump that might have shaped into the batter just a shade. Rossouw continues swinging but this time, does not quite pick the line or the length correctly. The ball breezes past the bat and pegs back middle stump!

name: S Dadswell
commentary: holes out to deep point! Short, wide and that deserved to be punished. Instead, Dadswell swings too hard at it and ends up slicing it straight down deep point's throat. That might have been a change-up too, and the way Dadswell played it, he might not have picked it up. Nevertheless, a consolatory wicket for the Super Kings!

name: D Brevis
commentary: loose shot from Brevis, and it gets his outside edge to first slip. Wild drive with a straight bat to a ball that was nipping away, giving Smuts a simple catch. Good work from Magala, and MICT's teenage star departs

name: RD Rickelton
shortText: c van der Merwe b Baartman
commentary: Slot ball is whipped, vd Merwe slides in from deep midwicket. Takes it smartly, sliding on his knees, took it fingers pointing up. Tumbled back on his head and almost did a headstand for a second.

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: Another slot ball induces a catch at deep midwicket. On middle, Roelofsen whips it with his back leg going up as he made contact. Didn't connect well, Cox ran in from the deep and took it on the move, low down in front. Excellent catch, lobbed it up casually as he glided back onto his feet. Two set batters out in the over with two balls to go.

name: GF Linde
commentary: Supreme reflexes help vd Merwe pluck a caught and bowled. Was shortish just outside off, Linde was cramped for room. He tried to flat bat it, didn't connect well but was going relatively quickly. Roelof swiftly stepped to his right, bent, kept his fingers up and mitted it.

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: Sweep beaten, stumps hit. Was around a length, didn't turn. May have kept a bit low, vd Dussen was in his crease but not in line. He missed and it hit middle and off, to Markram's delight.

name: SM Curran
shortText: c Markram b van der Merwe
commentary: Holed out to long-on. Curran out for a golden duck. He charged down, tried to whack the flick as hard as he could. Went flat and Markram took it comfortably.

name: AM Rossington
commentary: slower ball, and Rossington holed out to midwicket! Just couldn't quite time it and it's a comfortable catch

name: JT Smuts
commentary: little nudge and they run through for one, but a beautiful pick up and throw from Archer. Direct hit, and Smuts is gone. What a scintillating bit of fielding that is

name: SJ Erwee
commentary: rapped on the pads, angling in. That's very, very straight, and the umpire has no hesitation in raising the finger. Rabada strikes in the first over

name: AK Markram
commentary: Rashid Khan strikes first ball. Kevin Pietersen on commentary had been wondering why he wasn't in the attack. He bowls a quick yorker that beats Markram in the flight, and MICT are well on top now

name: T Stubbs
commentary: Slot ball does it again! Whipped flat in the air. Rickelton at deep midwicket takes it after a run to the right. Stubbs waited and got a decent chunk, but the timing wasn't good enough to over and the placement couldn't beat the fielder.

name: JM Cox
commentary: Direct hit, sent to the third umpire for a run-out check. Cox's bat is hovering low in the air despite being over the crease. A bit casual, the noise in the crowd gradually increase. Out it is. Bonus wicket for MI Cape Town. Jansen dropped the length ball behind square on the off side, quick throw and a bit of indifferent running by Cox, did not drag the bat in which costs him. Ball goes right up off the back of the bat after hitting the stumps. Excellent pick up on the move by Odean from short third, replays confirm, all in one motion.

name: M Jansen
commentary: Slower one knocks over Jansen! In the slot, at the stumps. Jansen's eyes lit up, went back in the crease and tried to slog it over midwicket. Misses. He's annoyed as he walks back but he's lit up the stadium in sunshine. He's toppled sense to deliver a special innings that can delight technicians and innovators alike. Leaves with four needed off six.

name: BA Carse
commentary: Pulled in the air, Archer runs across at deep midwicket, takes it! Slower one into the wicket, Carse cleared his front leg and looked to hit it as hard as possible. Got it off the edge, went up. Archer charged to his right and took it with a slide

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: Hendricks perishes! Dug into the track on middle and leg stump, and this one climbs onto Hendricks a lot quicker than he expects. He has an ugly hack at it and gets a tame top edge that lobs towards fine leg. Pretorius does the rest and cuts short Hendricks' slightly troubled vigil for the day!

name: F du Plessis
commentary: du Plessis bites the dust! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that bounces a touch extra and gets big on du Plessis. He looks to carve it over extra cover but does not quite get the control or the contact he wants. In the end, he splices it towards deep cover point, where Jacks does the rest!

name: D Ferreira
commentary: holes out to long on! Banged into the track, and angled across the batter. Ferreira tries to muscle it over long on but he is always working against the angle. He slices it towards long on, where Neesham settles himself under the high ball and sends Ferreira on his way!

name: R Shepherd
commentary: slower delivery on a length on leg stump. Shepherd has a massive mow across the line but is too early into the stroke. He gets plenty of height but not enough distance as Bosch runs back and completes the catch!

name: BS Makhanya
commentary: length delivery angled into the batter on leg stump. Makhanya looks to go inside out but again, gets too much underneath the ball. He spoons it towards extra cover, where Parnell does the rest! du Plooy is still off strike!

name: G Coetzee
commentary: oh my goodness! What a catch that is! Low full toss on off stump. Coetzee sits back in his crease and whips it towards deep mid wicket. Jacks runs around nonchalantly on the fence, flings out his right palm and plucks it out of thin air! He then tiptoes around the fence to ensure he does not step on the ropes too! Simply stunning!

name: PD Salt
commentary: in the air, and taken! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that sticks in the surface and spins away a touch. Salt gives himself room and looks to go inside out. The sluggishness off the surface, though, means that he slices it straight to deep cover point

name: WG Jacks
commentary: and he sends Jacks' off stump cartwheeling! Full and darted into off stump. Jacks tries to get a little too cute and looks for the scoop again. This time, though, he is late on the stroke and the ball goes past the bat before sending off stump flying out of the ground!

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: two in two for Joseph! The Super Kings are all over the Capitals like a rash now! Length delivery angled across the batter outside off stump. Rossouw has a very loose waft at it and only manages to feather it through to the keeper. The Capitals are in a spot of bother now!

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: huge appeal, and given! Very full delivery on leg stump. de Bruyn falls over a touch and then plays all around it. The ball strikes de Bruyn on the pads and on first glance, it looks as if it might have been sliding down leg. The umpire, though, does not think so! de Bruyn, understandably, wants to have another look! Nothing on Ultra Edge and Ball Tracking shows that the ball would have just clipped leg stump! Umpire's Call and de Bruyn has to walk back!

name: S Dadswell
commentary: cleans him up! And it is that man Phangiso again! Full delivery that slides into the batter on middle and leg stump. The ball continues with the arm, and skids through just enough to go past Dadswell's massive swing and crash into the stumps!

name: JDS Neesham
commentary: and Phangiso now knocks Neesham over! Oh my word! Slowed up a touch on a length on leg stump. This one just grips in the surface enough and spins back into Neesham. He has another slog across the line but this time, he misses. He hears the death rattle soon after, and the Super Kings are right back in this contest!

name: E Bosch
commentary: edged and taken! Coetzee has broken this game open, yet again! Back of a length delivery outside off stump. Bosch has another loose waft at it and after countless tries, he finally manages to nick one through to the keeper. Coetzee, the Super Kings and the thousands at the Wanderers are absolutely pumped!

name: M Pretorius
commentary: oh dear! This is pure hara-kiri! Low full toss on middle and leg stump. Parnell backs away and drills it towards mid off. He then dashes across to the other end, only to see his partner not interested in the single at all. In the end, Pretorius has to sacrifice himself, with Verreynne taking off the bails at the batter's end! That is a moment of absolute madness!

name: AU Rashid
commentary: in the air and taken at long off! Back of a length delivery outside off stump. Rashid looks to smash it over long off but is slightly late on the stroke. The ball pings off the splice towards du Plessis, who eats up ground to his right and holds onto a clutch catch!

name: A Nortje
commentary: Super Kings win! Look at the Super Kings go! Slower delivery dug into the track outside off stump. Nortje comes down the track and swings wildly, but only in vain! And that is well inside the tramlines too! In fact, Nortje has nicked that through to the keeper! The Super Kings have held their nerve here, and have send thousands of fans at the Wanderers into absolute delirium!

name: JJ Roy
commentary: Grubber or was Roy just stuck on his crease? Went quite low. It was off a length, came in straight. Roy was setting up on the back foot, tried to lower the straight bat in the last second but fell over and the bal rattled furniture.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Maharaj outsmarts and outskills Buttler. He claps zealously in celebration. Was similar to the last ball. Buttler came down early, Maharaj pulled his length back and hung it outside off. Buttler opened the face and tried to push it on the move. Misses it this time, easy stumping for QDK.

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: bowled 'im! Top of off does the job for Topley and DSG. Perfect length and just a hint of nip back in off the deck, beats Lubbe's wild hack and sends him back for a well-crafted 57 off 36

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: tossed up wide of off stump, Vilas sweeps... and feathers through to de Kock! Immediate celebration from Subrayen and up goes the finger. Vilas was looking to manufacture a shot into the leg side, the ball stayed a touch low and grazed the bottom edge through to the keeper

name: DA Miller
commentary: smacked to deep midwicket! Pretorius gets the danger man, as Miller drags a big hit straight to the man on the boundary rope. Pace off and he couldn't generate the power to get it all the way

name: EJG Morgan
commentary: Morgan holes out! Limp innings from the former England captain, looking for that favoured leg-side pick-up but doesn't get hold of it, and presents a dolly of a catch to deep midwicket

name: KR Mayers
commentary: Soft, soft caught and bowled. Mayers tried to clip the slow, shortish ball angling away, to the stumps, but got a leading edge. Dolly accepted by Fortuin.

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: Slog sweep again, not connected perfectly this time! Taken at deep square leg! This looked full, and Mulder saw it early but probably went after it too early. Got it off the bottom, in the air to the fielder. He's distraught. Shamsi enthusiastically high-fives Buttler, plucks out the stumps and uses it like a walking stick, holds onto his hamstring and signals to the dressing room - probably the physios - in celebration.

name: Q de Kock
commentary: Inside edge off the pull, off stump rocked back!. Fortuin was around the wicket. The ball was slightly back of length angling away to fourth. De Kock rocked back and tried to pull it in front of square. Thin edge took it onto the stumps, bails take a flight. De Kock smiles in resignation as the bowler celebrates.

name: D Pretorius
commentary: Inside edge found or has it? Buttler is interested in the review. They have reviewed. A very subtle signal from buttler, not a proud T normally seen. Looks like the ball hit the top of the back pad before hitting bat. Length ball just outside off, Impact three-fourth of the way up middle. It's hitting! Fortune favours Fortuin. Resigned smile from Pretorius who has to walk back. Royals are chuffed, excellent review. It came in, looked like spin. Pretorius was stuck in his crease and couldn't account for the angle in, he was trying to dab it late with an open face towards short third. Got hit on the pad before it hit bat.

name: JO Holder
commentary: slugged... but he picks out the boundary rider! Bowled into the pitch again and Holder doesn't quite get the yardage on his pull. Struck firmly and flat towards deep midwicket, but it's taken above his head by that man Fortuin

name: C Jonker
shortText: c sub (M Van Buuren) b Jones
commentary: short and lumped to deep square leg! Jones bags another and this tall chase just gets taller for DSG. Jonker took on the pull but didn't get enough of it, straightforward grab for the man coming in off the rope

name: KA Maharaj
commentary: swings to leg... straight to cow corner! Not the connection Maharaj was looking for and it's well held above his head by Roy, a few yards in from the rope. Jones roars in celebration after claiming his third wicket

name: GC Viljoen
commentary: clubbed downtown, taken on the run! Brilliant from Miller and Jones has two in two! Full ball and he got under the shot, it hung in the air as Miller an around from long-off, then swooped to take it smoothly. Royals closing in

name: D Brevis
commentary: Brevis' luck runs out finally! The celebrations tell you the entire story. Just the pressure of it all. Slightly short, he goes back into his crease and drills the pull. But, Brevis does not get enough elevation and slams it straight down the throat of deep midwicket. Ends a struggle for Brevis.

name: RD Rickelton
commentary: Cries of catch it and Sunrisers get their first wicket! Back of length ball that skids onto Rickelton quickly. He looks to help it away, but gets it off the splice with the ball going as far as the midwicket region. The fielder runs across from mid-on and takes it comfortably.

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: Another one bites the dust! Not Brevis, but Roelofsen it is, who falls. Keeps it homing on a length on off. He dances down looking for a wild heave. Can only drag it to midwicket who takes a simple catch.

name: SM Curran
commentary: And, another! Sunrisers have brought out their A game today! Markram does the damage. Fires it quick on off and middle stump.. Wasn't all that short, as Curran looks to play the cut hard. Gets a thick edge and Rossington takes a very good catch behind the stumps.

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: Straight, full and Magala strikes with a pin-point yorker! Or, does he? RVD has taken the review. The umpire's finger was up straight away. Did he get an edge on it? Oh, no, he did not. RVD misses and the ball-tracker confirms the leg stump would have taken a beating. Nelson strikes. End of a sprightly knock from RVD.

name: OF Smith
commentary: Miscues the back of a length ball, and that will test the fielder again. But Fuller does really well to hold on. Smith was going only one way. Looks to slam it away. Ends up dragging it to deep midwicket who runs in, settles himself and takes very good catch.

name: D Potgieter
commentary: Sunrisers keeps striking! Back of a length seam-up ball around middle and leg. He looks to flick it squarer, but gets a massive top-edge with the ball going straight up. Jansen gets around and takes a good catch around the short fine leg region.

name: Rashid Khan
commentary: Cleans him up last ball with a change of pace! Great comeback from Baartman in the last three balls. Rolls the fingers across the length ball on off. Rashid gets low to swing it away, misses and the off bail goes for a toss, and is in fact, broken.

name: AM Rossington
commentary: Soft dismissal, caught at mid-on to start proceedings! The pitch has been two-paced at times, it was this time. Came in a bit too. Rossington tried to push the fullish ball with a straight bat and was early on it, ended up scooping it, bottom hand came off and it was a dolly for Rabada at mid-on. First time ever there's a first-ball wicket in the SA20

name: JT Smuts
commentary: Full ball hits pad, given LBW. Smuts reviews. Was this going outside off? It was very full, pitched around middle and off, Smuts looked to whack it over long-on. Missed it, hit him on the knee-roll of the bent back leg after missing the inside edge. It's pitching on off, coming in just a bit. Impact: umpire's call, wickets: umpire's call. Smuts shakes his head as he walks, the fielders celebrate. Tad unlucky but it may have shaped in just a bit. Curran on a roll.

name: SJ Erwee
commentary: Massive LBW appeal, umpire takes his time... and gives it. Erwee has a word and sends it upstairs. You don't sweep Rashid, do you? But is this going down leg? The full ball is pitching on leg, spins in just a bit and just over half of the ball is hitting leg stump. Three reds. Erwee went for the hard sweep, missed it and has to leave, he's disappointed but gets a rousing reception from the home crowd.

name: AK Markram
commentary: Of course, Markram middles it perfectly even when he holes out. Got a short ball at the body, picked it and went bang. The ball went flat and deep midwicket was perfectly placed to catch the bullet

name: T Stubbs
commentary: Keeper celebrates, Odean looks disappointing. Stubbs is walking, kicking the ground and punching his bat furiously! Back-of-a-length missile, absolutely sizzled off the pitch. Stubbs went for the pull. Got a thin under edge. Another twist.
