name: JM Cox
commentary: Huge LBW appeal, turned down early. Goes to the short-third fence. Review taken. Looked plumb if there was no edge. Bat has hit pad as he went to flick the full ball pitching around off and coming in. The seam was curving in, the bat hit pad and turned 90 degrees, the outside edge was facing the bowler. Three cherry reds. Impact was on middle, hitting inner-half of leg stump. Odean Smith might just have turned this on its head.

name: KR Mayers
commentary: Edge off the pull goes to the keeper, Mayers misses out on the fifty but has played his part. Jones is punching in celebration. Was a slower one over the stumps. Mayers tried to go fine, it bounced a bit higher than the batter expected, rose off the edge and Buttler took an easy catch.

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: Does not get hold of it and Miller gobbles up a simple catch at long on! Slower low full toss well outside off. Mulder gets across, looking to clear long on. But he loses his shape with the bat turning in his hands and can only find Miller, who comes forward and takes the catch. Mulder did his job, though.

name: Q de Kock
commentary: Oh, that's a top catch from Jones running to his left from short third! Slower, length ball from Ngidi - was about 109kph. De Kock looks for a massive swipe, but is beaten by the pace and gets a massive top edge. Jones runs to his left, and also has to deal with the point fielder. He keeps his cool and puts in a dive to hold on.

name: KMA Paul
commentary: Slower back of a length delivery around the hip-area. He swivels and looks for a pull but can only manage a top-edge with the ball going straight up. Ngidi runs down in his follow-through and completes a simple catch.

name: JJ Roy
commentary: Subrayen's 100 kph top-of-the-stumper knocks over Roy. Was flat into the pitch, on a length, maybe slightly back. Roy shaped and went for the pull, got a low edge as he was crouching, looked like it went lower than he expected. Hits furniture and Subrayen pumps his chest.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Topley topples Buttler, length ball hits the top of the bails, sends them on a flight! Buttler made room and looked to pummel it off the back foot through midwicket, but the ball went further away with the angle, beat bat. Topley runs with his wings out in celebration.

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: Top-edged pull goes up... taken at long-on. No-ball check going on, it's fine. Pretorius landed it on a length, wide outside off at 120 kph. Lubbe tried to pull it across, got it off the bottom-half of the bat, easy catch to Holder

name: DA Miller
commentary: Skied, taken by Holder at long-on. Holder settled well and took it with the reverse cup. It was the slower ball, looked to be in the slot, but the deception took the pump down the ground right up

name: EJG Morgan
commentary: Oh, that is top work from Mulder and Morgan is run out! Fuller delivery outside off, he drills the drive to extra cover, who fires in a throw on the bounce to the bowler. Wasn't the best of throws, but Mulder does really well to get behind the stumps and take off the bails. Morgan was nowhere in the picture. Is that the game?

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: Another one or is that a no-ball again? It is a close one again. I think this is fine. Just about. Yep, the third umpire agrees. A full toss on the stumps, he is crouched and helps it to Dala at deep square leg, who catches it and throws it back quickly anticipating a no-ball. But, it is touch and go, and the third umpires goes with the bowler. Dane Vilas is not impressed. That's out, he asks and goes on his way,

name: E Jones
commentary: High, goes very hiiiigh and Junior Dala, the substitute fielder judges the catch to perfection . A cross-seam length ball on the pads from Topley. He flicks and gets a lot of elevation but not enough distance and the catch is taken at deep square leg.

name: FD Adams
commentary: Gets his man straight away! On a length well outside off. He was looking to heave it away, but gets it off the outside edge of his blade and deep point runs in to complete a simple catch.

name: JN Malan
commentary: Crucial breakthrough! Pressure was building up and he he hands a simple catch to mid-on who didn't have to move a muscle! Manufactures pace for himself but did'n't get all of it. Excellent bowling from Linde and brilliant move from Rashid Khan to continue with him for another over

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: You just felt like wicket was around the corner as he hits the bull's eye! Off-stump goes cartwheeling and Hendricks departs early in the piece. That's brilliant bowling from Rabada! Hits the perfect length and gets enough movement to wreck the stumps

name: F du Plessis
commentary: Brute of a delivery! Quicker delivery on a nagging line and length, turns sharply and there is a big gap between bat and bowl, sounds the death rattle and Waqar is absolutely ecstatic

name: K Verreynne
commentary: Cries of catch and taken! Length ball, stuck in the pitch and rises sharply, he plays all around it as he tries to smother the spin, Linde induces another error with his cunning spinning methods, it's turning out to be a fantastic over for MI Cape Town

name: JL du Plooy
commentary: Fraction short and slants into middle stump, gets the ball to rise sharpy off the deck as he goes for the hook and Ryan Rickleton takes a stunning catch at deep square, as easy as you like

name: D Ferreira
commentary: Rashid knocks him over! Fuller and angling into the batter at the stumps as he was loading up for a big heave over midwicket and the ball breezes past the bat and thuds into the leg stump, that's vintage Rashid

name: R Shepherd
commentary: Fires in a thunderbolt and Shepherd is caught at cover, shorter rising delivery, cramping him for room and he gets in an awkward position and gives a simple catch. It has been a real struggle for JSK thus far as they fail to up the ante

name: AS Joseph
commentary: High in the air and taken by Brevis at long-on who came charging in and pouching it safely! Just threw his bat at it and found no timing as he tried a massive hack

name: G Coetzee
commentary: My word! What a scorching delivery, length ball, plugging away in the corridor, takes the outside edge and Coetzee goes after scoring a run as JSK stare into the abyss.

name: D Brevis
commentary: Back of a length delivery just outside off stump, he stands tall and tries to clear long-on but it goes straight down Phangiso's throat, got the elevation but not the distance and Coetzee is absolutely pumped up! He plays with his heart on his sleeve

name: RD Rickelton
commentary: Length ball, getting just a hint of movement off the pitch and he throws his bat at it, wild swing and ends up getting the splice of the bat as Joseph gobbles it gleefully at third man

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: MICT need to chae in 16 overs to get the bonus point as Roelofsen mistimes the shot and hands a regulation catch straight to Malan at extra cover who didn't have to move a muscle. It's not easy to time the ball on this track

name: PD Salt
commentary: Magala strikes! Short of length ball on the middle, traps Salt lbw as he tries to work it towards offside. He immediately reviews. Ultra Edge confirms there was no bat involved. And Ball Tracking returns with three reds. Big blow for Capitals

name: WG Jacks
commentary: Out for 92! Jansen strikes for Sunrisers. Short delivery, pitched on the middle, Jacks goes for a pull and doesn't get the timing right as the keeper completes the catch. What a knock this has been from Jacks!

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: Two down Full delivery around off, he tries to slice it and gets a thick edge to keeper. Rossouw out for 20

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: De Bruyn departs! Full and around off, tries to scoop it over keeper but there is hardly any timing on that one as Cox completes an easy catch. A 23-ball 42 for de Bruyn!

name: JDS Neesham
commentary: Bowled! Yorker outside off, Neesham tries to drag and fails as the ball hits the stumps

name: WD Parnell
commentary: Two in a rowBaartman roars in celebration. Changes his angle, and bowls a back of a length delivery on the middle, Parnell misses and it hits the middle stump

name: SJ Erwee
commentary: Chips a drive to mid-off and Parnell's Ronaldo celebration is on! It was full, there for the drive and Erwee did not check the shot. He tried to hit it firmly with an ever so slightly open face. Not sure if he wanted to go wider or along the ground. Ends up giving a low catch to Jacks

name: JT Smuts
commentary: LBW given, looked straight. Batters discuss and Smuts eventually reviews. But there's confusion as to whether the review was late. No, all okay. Was a slower one into the pitch, it beat the flick. Hit just over the knee roll. No contact with the bat. Hawk-Eye shows three reds. Smuts goes. Impact was three-fourth of the way up middle, and the ball in the projection hit a chunk at the top of middle and leg.

name: JM Cox
commentary: Nicked off to the keeper and Parnell now goes for Ronaldo's jump celebration. He's on a hat-trick now. It was around a length just outside off, angling away. Cox looked to steer it with an open face and got a bottom edge.

name: AK Markram
commentary: Skier, very very high. Juggling act at long-on, taken on the third attempt. Massive wicket!. Slow, full and wide. Markram went across and slogged it. Tried to go over long-on/wide long-on. Got it right up, lots of air time. Pretorius tried to take it front, it popped out to the side, he managed to pull it up again, got it off the third attempt, close to the ground

name: T Stubbs
commentary: Stubbs is bowled by a very full ball! Tossed up generously, Stubbs cleared the path as he made room, saw it floating around the stumps. Tried to slap it through extra, went off the bottom into middle and off. The collapse is on now. Thin deflection back onto the stumps, replays show.

name: MJ Ackerman
commentary: You miss I hit stuff, from around the wicket. Fullish ball pitches around off and zips in, Ackerman tried to slog it across the line. Off stump was shaken and the off bail flew. No celebrations from Nortje, he just completed his bowling run.

name: JK Fuller
commentary: Tossed up at 78 kph and it promptly induces the top edge. Taken at long-off. Fuller cleared the front leg and tried to slash it over extra but it skied up and was taken comfortably. Replay shows the ball spun away which took it wide of the sweet spot

name: D Brevis
commentary: knocks him over with an absolute beauty! Searing yorker that starts well outside off stump before boomeranging back into the batter. Brevis has no clue about it and is late on the stroke too. The ball sneaks underneath the bat and flattens middle and off stump! Just the start the Super Giants were after!

name: RD Rickelton
commentary: strangled down the leg side! Dug into the track on leg stump, and Rickelton looks to help that one fine. He gets cramped for room a touch, though, meaning that he helps it straight into the gloves of de Kock! Not the best delivery Topley will bowl all tournament but he will not mind this wicket one bit!

name: G Roelofsen
commentary: Holder outfoxes Roelofsen! Another off-pace delivery on a length on leg stump. Roelofsen does not quite pick the variation and swings too early. The ball spirals off the leading edge and swirls towards short third man, where Topley does the rest!

name: HE van der Dussen
commentary: in the air, and taken! Flighted on a full length outside off stump. van der Dussen's eyes light up and he comes down the track. He has a massive mow across the line but because he is not to the pitch of the ball, he ends up dragging it. The sweeper at deep mid wicket settles himself and completes the catch!

name: SM Curran
commentary: that looks plumb! Slightly flatter and fuller. Curran, because of the trajectory, goes back and is trapped on the crease. He has a hopeful stab at it but misses it completely as the ball raps him on the back pad. The umpire raises his finger but Curran wants to have another look! . Flat line on Ultra Edge as the ball passes the bat. And Ball Tracking returns with three reds. Curran has to walk back!

name: GF Linde
commentary: what a catch! Short and wide outside off stump. Linde looks at the width and tries to carve it over backward point. He gets a decent piece of it but hits it close enough to the fielder, who leaps into the air and completes a sharp catch! Pretorius timed his jump superbly there!

name: Rashid Khan
commentary: in the air, and Rashid bites the dust! Length delivery pushed across the batter outside off stump again. Rashid looks to access the leg side but can't get enough whip on the stroke. The ball skews off the top edge and goes miles up in the air. Maharaj at short third man settles himself under the high ball and completes a smart grab!

name: D Potgieter
commentary: gone this time! Length at the stumps and Potgieter can't believe his luck. He has a mighty swing at it but because he is so eager to hit it over the fence, he loses shape. In the end, he chalks it towards long on, where the fielder gobbles up the chance!

name: KR Mayers
commentary: Linde gets Mayers! Back of a length delivery just outside off stump that spins into the batter. Mayers is neither forward nor back, and has a loose dab at it. The ball grazes the inside edge and Roelofsen does brilliantly to hold onto the chance!

name: Q de Kock
commentary: de Kock perishes! Back of a length delivery outside off stump. de Kock shuffles across and looks for the cute lap past short fine leg. He gets too much bat, though, and hits it straight to the fielder in the ring, who makes no mistake!

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: stumps flying everywhere! Searing yorker slanted into middle and off stump. Mulder backs away and looks to carve it past backward point. He is late on the stroke, though, and can't jam his bat down in time. The ball whistles past the bat before leaving middle and off stump in an almighty mess!

name: H Klaasen
commentary: what a catch, my word! Length delivery outside off stump that seems to stick in the surface a touch. Klaasen looks to fetch it and whip it over square leg but the lack of pace means that he top edges it. Rickelton runs back from inside the ring, dives full-length and plucks a stunning catch!

name: D Pretorius
commentary: huge appeal, and given! Drama at Newlands! Full delivery on middle and off stump that nips back sharply. Pretorius falls over a touch and then misses his flick. The ball raps him right in front of the stumps and the umpire raises his finger! No bat involved, and three reds on Ball Tracking! Pretorius perishes!

name: JN Malan
commentary: Raps him on the pad as Malan misses his sweep and the umpire raises his finger! Malan reviews immediately. Fired in quick and full around off, Malan got down to sweep and missed his shot and was hit on the front pad. No bat, and it's three reds on DRS so Joburg lose their first wicket and a review.

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: Second wicket in the over! Fortuin fired it flat on a length, Hendricks came down the track and had a swipe at it, but it came off the top edge and the ball went high in the air. David Miller did well to get under it and take a sliding catch. Joburg have lost both openers rather cheaply again

name: F du Plessis
commentary: Straight down deep third's throat! Faf du Plessis comes down the track to another length ball from Ngidi and gets a massive top edge that goes straight to Lubbe, who holds on to it comfortably

name: K Verreynne
commentary: Verreynne misses the reverse sweep and the umpire has raised the finger! That was tossed up quicker on off, with the ball spinning in sharply. Stays under the bat and hits him on the front pad. Verreynne reviews it, but that's three reds and Joburg's slide continues.

name: L Gregory
commentary: Bowled him through the gate! Fortuin tosses it up on a length around off, Gregory was playing for the spin but it goes straight and through the gap between his bat and pad. Fortuin has his third!

name: D Ferreira
commentary: Timberrrrrr! Evan Jones goes on a length on off and Ferreira misses his swing as the ball hits the top of leg to take the bails off. With that, Joburg are five down and in big trouble!

name: R Shepherd
commentary: Misses his flick, and that is plumb! Full on off, he misses his flick and is hit straight in front. Umpire raised his finger immediately and he can't review, as they don't have any left!

name: GHS Garton
commentary: Chopped on! Evans bangs it in short outside off and Garton goes for the cut but can only get an inside edge on to the stumps. That's nine gone for Joburg and Paarl will be thrilled!

name: AS Joseph
commentary: Castled! Adams goes full and the ball stayed low. Joseph looked to defend, but it went through the gap to hit leg stump. Joseph falls for 13 and Joburg are eight down

name: AM Phangiso
commentary: Edged behind and taken! Bangs it in on a length outside off, Phangiso looks to cut but only manages an edge and Jos Buttler dives to his right to gobble that up and that wraps up Joburg's innings in the 18th over.

name: JJ Roy
commentary: Dear me, he has guided it straight to deep third! Was he trying to go a bit finer? Banged in short, shoulder-high outside off. He arches back and ramps, but gets good enough connection for the ball to go straight down the throat of deep third. He was hitting them well, and probably that has brought about his downfall today.

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: Tries it again, but this time can only find point, where Joseph gobbles it up! Back of a length outside off, he looks for the previous shot, but this time there isn't as much room. He goes through with the shot and can only slice it for an easy catch.

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: Steps down the track, gets a lot of height but enough distance as long on pouches a simple catch! Tossed up nicely from Phangiso on middle, he looks to get under it but isn't anywhere near the pitch. He does not get the desired connection and Shepherd takes a simple catch.

name: WG Jacks
commentary: edged and taken! Back of a length delivery hung way outside off stump. Jacks follows it away from his body and does well to reach it actually. But that means he can only feather it through to the keeper, who takes that one in front of first slip!

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: in the air, and taken! Back of a length delivery on middle and leg stump that cramps the batter for room and also hurries onto him a touch. Rossouw is late on the stroke and gets a top edge that lobs tamely towards backward point. The Capitals are in some early trouble now!

name: TB de Bruyn
commentary: knocks him over with a ripper! Length delivery in the channel that decks back into the batter sharply. de Bruyn looks for the drive on the up and does so without foot movement, leaving a gap between bat and pad. The ball breezes through that gap and then flattens middle stump!

name: S Muthusamy
commentary: taken comfortably at deep mid wicket! Given a bit of air on a full length just outside off stump. Muthusamy has a swipe across the line but does not quite get to the pitch of the ball. It skews off the top edge and lobs towards deep mid wicket, where Jansen takes a comfortable catch!

name: S Dadswell
commentary: two in two for Markram! Length delivery on middle and leg stump that seems to hold in the surface a touch. Dadswell looks to heave it over cow corner but is early into the stroke. The ball spoons up off the top edge and Baartman does the rest at short fine leg!

name: JDS Neesham
commentary: holes out to long on! Low full toss slanted across the batter outside off stump. Neesham looks to fetch it and deposit it over long. The angle, though, means that he toe-ends it straight to long on, where Markram dives forward and completes the catch!

name: JT Smuts
commentary: Rashid gets Smuts! Quicker and flatter outside off stump again. Smuts looks to go leg side but the angle is always against him. In the end, he slices it straight to backward point, where Bosch makes no mistake!

name: SJ Erwee
commentary: Parnell breaks through! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that sticks in the surface and shapes away a touch too. Erwee looks to work it to leg but ends up getting a tame leading edge that is gobbled up by Jacks at mid off!

name: JM Cox
commentary: another very soft dismissal! Back of a length delivery at the stumps that holds in the surface, and it looks like Cox has not read the knuckle-ball either.. Cox is too early into the stroke and chips it straight down mid on's throat!

name: AK Markram
commentary: straight to the fielder! Length angled into the batter on middle and leg stump. Markram's eyes light up and he looks to whip it over deep square leg. This time, though, he does not quite get the timing he desires and hits it straight to deep square leg!

name: T Stubbs
commentary: cleans him up with a 151 kph corker! Full and fast at the stumps. Stubbs looks to tonk that one into next week but he is just too late on the stroke. The ball breezes past the bat and then thunders into off stump! The bails go flying, and that is just the wicket the Capitals needed!

name: JN Malan
commentary: another very soft dismissal! Full toss outside off stump and Malan could have hit that literally anywhere. Instead, he has a loose waft at it and clinks it straight to the fielder in the ring at extra cover. The Super Kings are now in a spot of bother!

name: RR Hendricks
commentary: soft dismissal! Tossed up on a full length on leg stump and that one sticks in the surface just enough to get the better of Hendricks. He closes the bat face early too, and is deceived in the air, offering a tame catch to Maharaj, who dives forward and sends Hendricks on his way!

name: F du Plessis
commentary: holes out to deep mid wicket! Back of a length delivery on leg stump that sticks in the surface ever so slightly. du Plessis looks to go over cow corner but the lack of pace means that he mistimes it a touch. Mayers makes up ground to his left and completes a smart catch!

name: K Verreynne
commentary: Verreynne bites the dust! Flighted on a length outside off stump, and it seems like Verreynne has not quite picked the flight well. He tries to help it into the leg side but does not get to the pitch of the ball at all. The ball also sticks in the surface and takes the leading edge before nestling into Maharaj's palms at point!

name: L Gregory
commentary: another leading edge, and another batter perishes! Flighted beautifully on a length outside off stump. Gregory, much like Verreynne, is not to the pitch of the ball, yet, tries a swish across the line. The ball flies off the leading edge and lobs towards point, where the fielder does the rest!

name: R Shepherd
commentary: knocks him over! Slower yorker at the stumps that dips and drops on the batter very late. Shepherd swings for the hills but is always too early into the stroke. The ball squirms past the bat and kisses the top of middle and off stump!

name: KR Mayers
commentary: length delivery angled across the batter just outside off stump. Mayers has another mighty swing at it, only to connect with fresh air. He seems to over-balance a touch, and Verreynne quickly whips off the bails. In fact, Verreynne is quite confident he has gotten his man! Indeed! There is nothing behind the line when the ball are taken off, and Mayers has to go!

name: Q de Kock
commentary: soft dismissal! And guess who has broken this game open? Yes, it is Ferreira! Slowed up a touch on a full length on leg stump. de Kock looks to work to leg but closes his bat face just a tad early. The ball spoons up off the leading edge and Ferreira completes a fairly regulation return catch!

name: H Klaasen
commentary: in the air, and taken! Klaasen perishes! Back of a length delivery on leg stump that rushes onto Klaasen and gets big on him. He looks to muscle it over mid off but only manages to clink it straight to du Plessis! Another massive moment in the game!

name: PWA Mulder
commentary: and Siboto repays du Plessis' faith! High full toss outside off stump. Mulder swings at it because he has no other option. He loses his shape, though, and slices it badly. Phangiso settles himself at extra cover and completes the catch! The umpires confer with each other about it being a No ball for height before sending Mulder on his way!

name: D Pretorius
commentary: searing yorker on middle and leg stump. Pretorius walks across his stumps and in the end, is unable to access the ball. It kisses the outside of the pad and then flies through to the keeper. Joseph appeals for the lbw, and sees the umpire raise his finger too! Nothing on Ultra Edge, and Ball Tracking returns with three reds! Pretorius has to make the long walk back!

name: WJ Lubbe
commentary: Archer breaks through! Back of a length delivery on middle and leg stump that hurries onto the batter. Lubbe has a swipe across the line but is awfully late on the stroke. The ball pings off the higher part of the bat and lobs towards mid on, where Linde runs in and completes a superb catch diving forward!

name: JC Buttler
commentary: cleans him up! Full toss that hones in on the stumps. Buttler walks across his stumps and looks for the cute lap over the keeper. He is just a little late on the stroke, though, and for once, misses his lap stroke. The ball breezes past the bat and smashes into middle stump!

name: JJ Roy
commentary: in the air, and taken! Length delivery just outside off stump and Roy continues swinging. This time, too, he is early into the stroke and toe-ends it horribly. The ball goes miles up towards mid on, where Rashid settles himself and completes the catch!

name: DJ Vilas
commentary: middle stump has been knocked out of the ground! Length delivery on middle and off stump that nips back sharply. Vilas has a waft at it without any foot movement and leaves a massive gap between bat and pad. The ball exploits that space and flattens middle stump!

name: DA Miller
commentary: straight to the fielder! Dug into the track on middle and leg stump. Miller backs away and looks to thump it over deep cover point. He does not quite get the elevation, though, and despite hitting the shorter boundary, he hits it straight down the sweeper's throat

name: EJG Morgan
commentary: yorker outside off stump. Morgan drills it down to long off, and has no option but to go for the second. Fortuin makes it comfortably at the bowler's end but Morgan is a couple of yards short at the other end. Sums up the Royals' innings today!

name: FD Adams
commentary: two in two for Archer! Superb slower delivery on a full length just outside off stump, and Adams has no clue about this one. He is at least a week early into the stroke and clinks it. The ball lobs tamely towards extra cover, where Rickelton does the rest!

name: RD Rickelton
commentary: knocks him over! Full, fast and angling into the batter at the stumps. Rickelton is taken aback by the pace and is horribly late on the stroke. The ball breezes past the bat, kisses the pad and then sends off stump flying! What a comeback by the youngster!

name: SM Curran
commentary: high in the air, and taken at long on! Length delivery just outside off stump. Curran has a massive hack at it but looks like he has not quite picked the slower one. He slices it miles up into the air towards long on, where Miller settles himself and completes the catch!
